metadata.description: Base Pokemon data for Generation I (Red/Blue/Yellow). Game-specific encounter data stored separately.

001.name: Bulbasaur
001.pokedexEntry: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokemon.

002.name: Ivysaur
002.pokedexEntry: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

003.name: Venusaur
003.pokedexEntry: The flower on its back releases a soothing scent that enhances emotions.

004.name: Charmander
004.pokedexEntry: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

005.name: Charmeleon
005.pokedexEntry: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably hot levels.

006.name: Charizard
006.pokedexEntry: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

007.name: Squirtle
007.pokedexEntry: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

008.name: Wartortle
008.pokedexEntry: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

009.name: Blastoise
009.pokedexEntry: A brutal Pokemon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

010.name: Caterpie
010.pokedexEntry: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

011.name: Metapod
011.pokedexEntry: This Pokemon is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

012.name: Butterfree
012.pokedexEntry: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

013.name: Weedle
013.pokedexEntry: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

014.name: Kakuna
014.pokedexEntry: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokemon can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

015.name: Beedrill
015.pokedexEntry: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

016.name: Pidgey
016.pokedexEntry: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

017.name: Pidgeotto
017.pokedexEntry: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokemon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

018.name: Pidgeot
018.pokedexEntry: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

019.name: Rattata
019.pokedexEntry: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

020.name: Raticate
020.pokedexEntry: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

021.name: Spearow
021.pokedexEntry: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

022.name: Fearow
022.pokedexEntry: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

023.name: Ekans
023.pokedexEntry: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, whole.

024.name: Arbok
024.pokedexEntry: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

025.name: Pikachu
025.pokedexEntry: When several of these Pokemon gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

026.name: Raichu
026.pokedexEntry: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

027.name: Sandshrew
027.pokedexEntry: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

028.name: Sandslash
028.pokedexEntry: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

029.name: Nidoran♀
029.pokedexEntry: Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

030.name: Nidorina
030.pokedexEntry: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

031.name: Nidoqueen
031.pokedexEntry: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

032.name: Nidoran♂
032.pokedexEntry: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

033.name: Nidorino
033.pokedexEntry: An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

034.name: Nidoking
034.pokedexEntry: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

035.name: Clefairy
035.pokedexEntry: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

036.name: Clefable
036.pokedexEntry: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

037.name: Vulpix
037.pokedexEntry: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

038.name: Ninetales
038.pokedexEntry: Very smart and vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

039.name: Jigglypuff
039.pokedexEntry: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

040.name: Wigglytuff
040.pokedexEntry: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

041.name: Zubat
041.pokedexEntry: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

042.name: Golbat
042.pokedexEntry: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

043.name: Oddish
043.pokedexEntry: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

044.name: Gloom
044.pokedexEntry: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

045.name: Vileplume
045.pokedexEntry: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. It has the largest petals in the world.

046.name: Paras
046.pokedexEntry: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

047.name: Parasect
047.pokedexEntry: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

048.name: Venonat
048.pokedexEntry: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted to light at night.

049.name: Venomoth
049.pokedexEntry: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

050.name: Diglett
050.pokedexEntry: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It also appears above ground.

051.name: Dugtrio
051.pokedexEntry: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

052.name: Meowth
052.pokedexEntry: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

053.name: Persian
053.pokedexEntry: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

054.name: Psyduck
054.pokedexEntry: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.

055.name: Golduck
055.pokedexEntry: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

056.name: Mankey
056.pokedexEntry: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

057.name: Primeape
057.pokedexEntry: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

058.name: Growlithe
058.pokedexEntry: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

059.name: Arcanine
059.pokedexEntry: A Pokémon that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

060.name: Poliwag
060.pokedexEntry: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

061.name: Poliwhirl
061.pokedexEntry: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

062.name: Poliwrath
062.pokedexEntry: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

063.name: Abra
063.pokedexEntry: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and teleport to safety.

064.name: Kadabra
064.pokedexEntry: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

065.name: Alakazam
065.pokedexEntry: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

066.name: Machop
066.pokedexEntry: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

067.name: Machoke
067.pokedexEntry: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

068.name: Machamp
068.pokedexEntry: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

069.name: Bellsprout
069.pokedexEntry: A carnivorous Pokémon that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

070.name: Weepinbell
070.pokedexEntry: It spits out poison powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of acid.

071.name: Victreebel
071.pokedexEntry: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

072.name: Tentacool
072.pokedexEntry: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

073.name: Tentacruel
073.pokedexEntry: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

074.name: Geodude
074.pokedexEntry: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

075.name: Graveler
075.pokedexEntry: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing direction.

076.name: Golem
076.pokedexEntry: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

077.name: Ponyta
077.pokedexEntry: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

078.name: Rapidash
078.pokedexEntry: Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

079.name: Slowpoke
079.pokedexEntry: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

080.name: Slowbro
080.pokedexEntry: The Shellder that is latched onto Slowpoke's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.

081.name: Magnemite
081.pokedexEntry: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses Thunder Wave and similar moves.

082.name: Magneton
082.pokedexEntry: Formed by several Magnemite linking together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

083.name: Farfetch'd
083.pokedexEntry: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

084.name: Doduo
084.pokedexEntry: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

085.name: Dodrio
085.pokedexEntry: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head is said to stay awake.

086.name: Seel
086.pokedexEntry: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

087.name: Dewgong
087.pokedexEntry: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

088.name: Grimer
088.pokedexEntry: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

089.name: Muk
089.pokedexEntry: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

090.name: Shellder
090.pokedexEntry: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

091.name: Cloyster
091.pokedexEntry: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

092.name: Gastly
092.pokedexEntry: Almost invisible, this gaseous Pokémon cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

093.name: Haunter
093.pokedexEntry: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

094.name: Gengar
094.pokedexEntry: Under a full moon, this Pokémon likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

095.name: Onix
095.pokedexEntry: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

096.name: Drowzee
096.pokedexEntry: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

097.name: Hypno
097.pokedexEntry: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi powers such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

098.name: Krabby
098.pokedexEntry: Its pincers are not only powerful, they are so hard that they have a harder time breaking than diamond.

099.name: Kingler
099.pokedexEntry: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

100.name: Voltorb
100.pokedexEntry: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, they have zapped many people.

101.name: Electrode
101.pokedexEntry: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

102.name: Exeggcute
102.pokedexEntry: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

103.name: Exeggutor
103.pokedexEntry: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue living as an Exeggcute.

104.name: Cubone
104.pokedexEntry: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this Pokémon's real face.

105.name: Marowak
105.pokedexEntry: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

106.name: Hitmonlee
106.pokedexEntry: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

107.name: Hitmonchan
107.pokedexEntry: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

108.name: Lickitung
108.pokedexEntry: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

109.name: Koffing
109.pokedexEntry: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

110.name: Weezing
110.pokedexEntry: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 Koffings can fuse into a Weezing over many years.

111.name: Rhyhorn
111.pokedexEntry: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer truck flying.

112.name: Rhydon
112.pokedexEntry: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

113.name: Chansey
113.pokedexEntry: A rare and elusive Pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

114.name: Tangela
114.pokedexEntry: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.

115.name: Kangaskhan
115.pokedexEntry: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

116.name: Horsea
116.pokedexEntry: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

117.name: Seadra
117.pokedexEntry: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

118.name: Goldeen
118.pokedexEntry: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

119.name: Seaking
119.pokedexEntry: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

120.name: Staryu
120.pokedexEntry: An enigmatic Pokémon that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

121.name: Starmie
121.pokedexEntry: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

122.name: Mr. Mime
122.pokedexEntry: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

123.name: Scyther
123.pokedexEntry: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

124.name: Jynx
124.pokedexEntry: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

125.name: Electabuzz
125.pokedexEntry: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

126.name: Magmar
126.pokedexEntry: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

127.name: Pinsir
127.pokedexEntry: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

128.name: Tauros
128.pokedexEntry: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

129.name: Magikarp
129.pokedexEntry: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

130.name: Gyarados
130.pokedexEntry: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

131.name: Lapras
131.pokedexEntry: A Pokémon that has been overhunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across bodies of water.

132.name: Ditto
132.pokedexEntry: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

133.name: Eevee
133.pokedexEntry: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.

134.name: Vaporeon
134.pokedexEntry: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

135.name: Jolteon
135.pokedexEntry: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000-volt lightning bolts.

136.name: Flareon
136.pokedexEntry: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

137.name: Porygon
137.pokedexEntry: A Pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

138.name: Omanyte
138.pokedexEntry: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

139.name: Omastar
139.pokedexEntry: A prehistoric Pokémon that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

140.name: Kabuto
140.pokedexEntry: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

141.name: Kabutops
141.pokedexEntry: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

142.name: Aerodactyl
142.pokedexEntry: A ferocious, prehistoric Pokémon that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

143.name: Snorlax
143.pokedexEntry: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

144.name: Articuno
144.pokedexEntry: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

145.name: Zapdos
145.pokedexEntry: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

146.name: Moltres
146.pokedexEntry: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

147.name: Dratini
147.pokedexEntry: Long considered a mythical Pokémon until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

148.name: Dragonair
148.pokedexEntry: A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

149.name: Dragonite
149.pokedexEntry: An extremely rarely seen marine Pokémon. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

150.name: Mewtwo
150.pokedexEntry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

151.name: Mew
151.pokedexEntry: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
